The paper discusses stochastic variational inference (SVI) in Bayesian deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also presents results for Bayesian logistic regression and neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.NE) applications. Finally, the paper discusses numerical approximation and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the statistics (cs.ST) sub-category.
